definitions.definition: Chronologically first , early ; of or pertaining to the beginning , cause or origin.
examples: Our initial admiration for their efficiency gave way to disgust about their methods.
The initial stages of a syndrome may differ vastly from the final symptoms.

definitions.definition: Spatially first, placed at the beginning , in the first position ; especially said of the first letter of a word.
examples: The initial letter of names is usually printed with a capital letter.

main_definition: Chronologically first , early ; of or pertaining to the beginning , cause or origin.
secondary_definitions: Spatially first, placed at the beginning , in the first position ; especially said of the first letter of a word.
